guard-for-in.description:
Description

This rule is aimed at preventing unexpected behavior that could arise from using afor inloop without filtering the results in the loop. As such, it will warn whenfor inloops do not filter their results with anifstatement.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint guard-for-in: "error"*/

for (key in foo) {
    doSomething(key);
}

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint guard-for-in: "error"*/

for (key in foo) {
    if (Object.hasOwn(foo, key)) {
        doSomething(key);
    }
}

for (key in foo) {
    if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(foo, key)) {
        doSomething(key);
    }
}

for (key in foo) {
    if ({}.hasOwnProperty.call(foo, key)) {
        doSomething(key);
    }
}
